  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7, then take your <strong>chicken</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Put a large baking tray (or two) in the oven to heat up</p><p>Cut your <strong>potato[es]</strong> (skins on) into wedges, then peel and finely slice your <strong>red onion[s]</strong></p><p>Slice your <strong>chestnut mushrooms</strong> finely and chop your <strong>smoked streaky bacon</strong> roughly</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1665487735687-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1665487735687-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1665487735687-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1665487735687-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1665487735687-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add a handful of <strong>flour </strong>to a plate and a splash of <strong>milk </strong>to a shallow bowl</p><p>Add your <strong>panko breadcrumbs </strong>and <strong>half </strong>your <strong>ground paprika </strong>(you'll use the rest later!) to a separate plate with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>and mix it all together</p><p>Season your <strong>chicken breast strips</strong> with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong>, coat them in <strong>flour</strong>, tap off any excess, then add them to the <strong>milk </strong>and finally press them into the <strong>breadcrumbs </strong>firmly to coat evenly – these are your <strong>breaded chicken dippers</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1665487741560-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1665487741560-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1665487741560-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1665487741560-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1665487741560-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>potato wedges</strong> to one side of a baking tray with the <strong>remaining ground paprika</strong>, a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper </strong>and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Add the <strong>breaded chicken dippers </strong>to the other side of the baking tray (cooking for 3 or more? Use a separate tray!) and put the tray[s] in the oven for 20-25 min or until the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!) and the wedges are golden – these are your <strong>chicken dippers & wedges</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1690536190189-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1690536190189-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1690536190189-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1690536190189-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1690536190189-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>tomato paste</strong> to a bowl with a generous pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper </strong>and<strong> </strong>3 tbsp<span class=\"text-purple\"> [4 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[6 tbsp]</span> <strong>cold water</strong> and give everything a good mix up – this is your <strong>tomato sauce</strong></p><p>Drain your <strong>mozzarella</strong>, then pat it dry with kitchen paper (squeeze as much liquid out as you can)</p><p>Tear the <strong>drained mozzarella</strong> into rough, bite-sized pieces</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1665487753240-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1665487753240-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1665487753240-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1665487753240-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1665487753240-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your<strong> pizza base[s] </strong>to a separate baking tray (or two!)</p><p>Top the <strong>pizza base[s] </strong>with the <strong>tomato sauce </strong>and spread it evenly all over with the back of a spoon</p><p>Top with your <strong>sliced pepperoni</strong>, <strong>sliced onion</strong>, <strong>sliced mushrooms</strong>,<strong> chopped bacon </strong>and <strong>torn mozzarella </strong>and season with a pinch of <strong>pepper</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1665487758318-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1665487758318-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1665487758318-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1665487758318-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1665487758318-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for 13-15 min or until the cheese has melted and the base[s] is crisp – this is your <strong>meaty pizza[s]</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1665487771566-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1665487771566-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1665487771566-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1665487771566-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1665487771566-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the pizza is cooking, peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Combine the <strong>chopped garlic</strong> (not a big garlic fan? Try using less!) with your <strong>mayo</strong>, <strong>dried oregano</strong> and 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>cold water</strong> in a bowl<strong> </strong>–<strong> </strong>this is your <strong>garlic & herb dip</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-copy-1665487799568-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-copy-1665487799568-x400.jpg",
